items.name: Consent
items.label:
Hi,

Thank you for choosing to take part in this study.
We aim to examine the effect of daily interactions on your well-being.

__The Study and the Payment__
1. Entry Survey: A start questionnaire (appr. 25 minutes) including general information, and your relations to the Dutch. (0.5 Credits)
2. Experience Recaps: 30 days of short reflection surveys (appr. 2-4 minutes) on your interactions twice a day. (up to 4 Credits if you fill out all the Recaps)
3. Conclusion Survey: On the last day we will conclude with a final questionnaire (appr. 25 minutes) with some questions on your habits and a reflection of the study. (0.5 Credits)

**The payment will be determined based on your participation (e.g. how often you fill out the Experience Recaps) and will be transferred to your account once the study is concluded.**

__Your Privacy is Important__
Your participation is completely confidential and anonymous. No identifying information will be stored. Only members of the research team will have access to the survey data, but even they cannot link the data to any single person. Please feel free to answer all questions openly and honestly.

__Your Rights__
You can decide whether or not to participate in the study.
You can leave the study at any time.

__Risks__
There are no known risks associated with this study.
But please note that it is absolutely common and normal to not have social interactions every day.

__Questions__
We will be happy to answer questions about the study outcomes after your completion. Should you have technical questions or complaints feel free to contact us at:
j.kreienkamp@rug.nl (researcher) / k.epstude@rug.nl (supervisor).

items.name: InteractionInstr
items.label: This question, as well as the daily recaps, will be about your daily in-person interactions. By daily interactions, we mean a continued interaction with another person (potentially in a group) that lasts at least 10 minutes. For example, talking with a cashier at Albert Hijn checkout would not count as an interaction. If this interaction happens to last longer than 10 minutes, it would count as an interaction. Another example could be an Academic skills session. As this lasts longer than 10 minutes, it would count as an interaction. However, your interaction partner may be less clear as there are multiple people in the Academic Skills course. In this case, it would be great if you could answer the daily recaps keeping in mind the person that was most important to you (this could be the person giving the course as you interacted most with them but also your sitting neighbor as only together are these courses survivable; it really depends on your personal situation).

items.name: OutroTxt
items.label:
Thank you. You made it through the entry questionnaire. During the upcoming 4 weeks we will send you super short daily questionnaires - the Experience Recaps. They only take a couple of minutes and focus on the interactions you had with Dutch or non-Dutch people since the last Experience Recap. There will be two per day. We will send you one for the morning (at around noon) and one for the afternoon (at around 7 pm). To keep the timeframe consistent, each of the short Recaps will be accessible for seven hours. Keep in mind that answering the Recaps is only possible within these seven hours. Please also take the Recap even if you had no interactions at all. Note, that it is absolutely normal and common to not have interactions. Whether or not you had an interaction, morning or evening, each Recap is worth SONA credits. Payment of the daily Recaps:
Completion Recaps Time(est.) SONA
50% 30 1:45 hr 2 Cr.
75% 45 2:37 hr 3 Cr.
90%+ 54+ 3:09 hr 4 Cr.

Lastly, make sure to click "Submit" to finish this questionnaire and earn your first 0.5 SONA Credits. See you tomorrow. The Meeting the Dutch Team

items.label: ### Save date and measurement period
items.value:
ifelse(format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") > c("12:00") &&  format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") < c("19:00"),
                      paste(Sys.Date(),"Morning"),
                      ifelse(format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") > c("19:00") && format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") < c("23:59"),
                             paste(Sys.Date(),"Afternoon"),
                             paste(Sys.Date()-1,"Afternoon")))

items.name: period
items.label: ### Save daytime (incl. today or yesterday)
items.value:
ifelse(format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") > c("12:00") &&  format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") < c("19:00"),
                   "this morning",
                   ifelse(format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") > c("19:00") && format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") < c("23:59"),
                          "this afternoon",
                          "yesterday's afternoon"))

items.label: ### Save date and measurement period
items.value:

                      paste(Sys.Date(),"Morning"),
                      ifelse(format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") > c("19:00") && format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") < c("23:59"),
                             paste(Sys.Date(),"Afternoon"),
                             paste(Sys.Date()-1,"Afternoon")))

items.name: period
items.label: ### Save daytime (incl. today or yesterday)
items.value:
ifelse(format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") > c("12:00") &&  format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") < c("19:00"),
                   "this morning",
                   ifelse(format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") > c("19:00") && format(Sys.time(), "%H:%M") < c("23:59"),

units.subject: Conclusion Questionnaire and SONA Credits
units.body:
`r sample(c("Hi","Hey","Hello","Good morning"), 1, replace=TRUE)` `r AOTS_Pre$name`, You have reached the end of the study. There is only the conclusion questionnaire left. It will only take about 15 minutes. Really, we timed it :-) Once you have completed the conclusion questionnaire, you will receive your password for the SONA accreditation.
To the final questionnaire
Please make sure to follow the link as soon as possible. Note: For some, the SONA credits will be awarded towards the end of January to ensure that you also get your credits even if you are getting close to the SONA limit. Thanks again for all your amazing work, The Meeting the Dutch Team
